    I-perm-005 (#1199) slice 2: annotate_report_against_verdicts — keep + label (the always-release verb)
    
    Additive — INERT until the call-site flip (the existing redactor `reconcile_report_against_verdicts`
    is byte-unchanged; the 44 redactor tests pass). Under the always-release reframe a non-VERIFIED claim
    is KEPT and LABELED (user judges) instead of DELETED.
    
    `annotate_report_against_verdicts(report_text, final_verdicts, audit_map, marker_by_claim)`:
    - STRIPS any pre-existing confidence markers up front (idempotent re-run; deterministic markers are
      reproduced; fresh report = no-op), then collects every non-VERIFIED claim (validate + presence +
      `_claim_fully_pinnable`) and labels in a SINGLE PASS over the (marker-free) report. Sentence spans
      are computed ONCE off the unmutated text, so two non-VERIFIED claims on the SAME line each get
      their own marker — no appended marker can perturb another claim's segmentation (Codex iter-3 P0)
      and a re-run no longer collapses same-line spans (Codex iter-4 P1).
    - COMPLETENESS (Codex P0-1 + iter-2): `_claim_fully_pinnable` strips markers then runs the redactor
      TIER-1; a non-TIER-1 occurrence (multi-line OR same-line straddle / under-split) -> fail closed
      BEFORE labeling. Defensive post-pass: a pinnable claim that matched no sentence also fails closed.
      Never ships a non-VERIFIED claim unlabeled.
    - P0-2: shared `_prose_stem` byte-unchanged (marker strip is local), so a literal `[confidence: ...]`
      in report/audit text can never alter the redactor's normalization. Missing marker -> generic low
      fallback; genuinely-absent claim -> already_absent.
    
    Codex slice-2 diff gate iters 1-4 (partial-label leak, shared-_prose_stem mutation, completeness
    segmentation, same-line labeling perturbation, re-run idempotence) — all fixed by: pinnability on the
    marker-stripped pre-pass via redactor TIER-1; a single labeling pass off the unmutated text; and an
    up-front marker pre-strip.
    
    Tests (11): VERIFIED byte-identical + label UNSUPPORTED; marker after the sentence; missing-marker
    fallback; absent recorded; no-audit-row fails closed; verified-only no-op; multi-line + same-line
    straddle fail closed; two same-line claims both labeled; idempotent single + two-same-line re-run.
    44 redactor tests green.
    
    Next sub-step: flip the runner call site (annotate under PG_ALWAYS_RELEASE) + claim_confidence.json +
    report render; then the UI confidence chip.
    
